Pro-Level Polish Prompt (Use This As-Is)

Prompt:

Do a final polish pass on this band website to make it feel like a modern, high-end artist/label site. Keep the existing structure and features—this is a refinement, not a rebuild.

1. Motion & Interactions (High Priority)

Add subtle, smooth animations across the site:

Use ease-in-out timing and short durations (150–300ms)
Add:
Hover effects on cards (slight scale, brightness, or lift)
Smooth transitions for buttons and arrows
Scroll-based fade/slide-in for sections
Avoid anything flashy or distracting—keep it minimal and premium
2. Shows Section (Make It Feel Premium)
Add:
Smooth horizontal scrolling feel (slight easing)
Card hover:
Slight scale up
Soft shadow or glow
Active vs expired:
Active = crisp + responsive
Expired = dimmed but still clean (not ugly grey)
Improve spacing so cards feel intentional and evenly distributed
3. Gallery Section (Modern Feel)
Add:
Smooth transitions when images change/randomize
Slight zoom or parallax feel on hover
Ensure:
No layout shifting
Clean grid alignment at all times
Keep motion subtle and fluid
4. Video Section (Fix + Upgrade)
Ensure:
Correct aspect ratio (no stretching)
Proper centering
Add:
Clean responsive container
Optional subtle fade-in on load
Make it feel like a featured content block, not an afterthought
5. Typography & Spacing
Improve:
Consistent spacing between sections
Clean alignment across all elements
Slightly refine:
Font sizes
Letter spacing
Section hierarchy
6. Buttons & Arrows
Upgrade arrows:
Smooth hover transitions
Slight opacity/brightness shift on hover
Keep them minimal and not intrusive
Ensure they feel intentional and responsive
7. Performance-Safe Animations
Use:
CSS transforms (translate, scale, opacity)
Avoid:
Heavy JS animations
Layout-thrashing properties
8. Overall Feel

Goal:

Clean
Modern
Smooth
Slightly “music industry / label” aesthetic

Avoid:

Over-animating
Gimmicky effects
Anything that hurts performance
Constraints
Do NOT break existing functionality
Do NOT rewrite entire components
Keep code clean and modular
Only enhance what exists
Output
Return updated code only
No explanations unless necessary